        <abstract> 
<p>TH believes that the progeny of hybrid crosses, in which a domesticated or "artificial" race is involved, tend to resemble the more "natural" of their parents [see <hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>, p. 486].</p>  
<p>Provides some information on local hybrid domestic geese [see <hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>, p. 439] and pigeons.</p> 
        </abstract>
